      "content": "> Similar to other reports, suddenly after the update with ordering users, the GraphQL API is exposing the amount of > participants in a private program to non-invited users. This allows an attacker to retrieve the amount of participants in a private program, as well as their details.\n\nI guess I did not write this up properly, but after I noticed that in the GrapHQL schema, on the `team` object, the `order_by` selector was added, the `participants` attribute was exposing the hall of fame of private programs running policies in the external directory.\n\nThe updated HackerOne GraphQL schema can be found here: https://github.com/arkadiyt/bounty-targets-data/blob/master/data/hackerone_schema.graphql. It's frequently updated, so keep an eye on it.",
